    "The table is structured as follows: rows correspond to the input grid ratio π, matching the setup of table 1, while columns indicate the relative query grid size π sr.",
    "For instance, on the Advection dataset with an original grid size of 128, the second row (π = 50%) corresponds to 64 input points, and the third column (π sr = 400%) corresponds to querying 512 points.",
